Job Summary: 
This role is act as a HR generalist to work with HR Manager/Supervisor to integrate into business teams as a trusted partner to execute site operation HR matters, as well as to help diagnose problems, identity and drive appropriate solutions. Will also be an active member of People team to drive and support regional level and cross-department initiatives. The new HR generalist needs to provide HR service to MPS Shanghai &amp; Shenzhen site including but not limited to talent acquisition, learning, retention and other HR administration. This opening is a newly added headcount in China People team.
Responsibilities: 
1.	Translate strategic and tactical business plans into human resource plans &amp; roadmaps. Work closely with business leaders in improving the organization competence. An advisor to business leaders on human resources issues &amp; solutions;
2.	Demonstrate a strong commitment to achieve staffing objectives. Engage in timely and appropriate communications with all candidates, hiring managers, vendors, HR team members and other stakeholders;
3.	Based on company business development and organization needs, develop recruitment plan and fully support the implementation of recruitment projects, such as campus recruitment, intern recruitment, and etc.
4.	Support in deploying training and development initiative and programs. Establish yearly training plan based on company business development, qualification requirements and etc. Organize &amp; improve the orientation materials and conduct orientation training to all new hires on time;
5.	Drive structured approach, process &amp; gain momentum for leadership development, cross team collaboration, succession planning and workforce management in anticipation of emerging business need;
6.	Work closely with the Business Leaders and HR team to support and coordinate various HR engagement activities and other employer building programs to ensure employees have a great experience through the employee life cycle from onboarding to termination;
7.	Implement and communicate national policies &amp; projects &amp; practices on site to ensure fair and consistent treatment of employees, make sure all HR policies are up-to date and in compliance with government and local regulations and policies;
8.	In charge of on board / termination / internal transfer process, optimize internal process and develop best practice;
9.	Perform any other duties or special HR projects assigned by direct supervisor.
Requirements: 
1.	Bachelor degree or above in biz management or related major;
2.	At least 5 years’ HR experience in multinational company, 3+ years’ experience in an HR generalist or business partner role, Sales office experience is preferred;
3.	A good understanding about organization structure, people, business and future direction, know the trends in HR, labor market and business environment in China and / or globally;
4.	Able to deal with ambiguity &amp; pace of change;
5.	Excellent communication skills, good command of English and Office software;
6.	Ability to handle multi-project, balance priorities and meet deadlines.

岗位职责:
1.负责招聘渠道维护、简历筛选、电话邀约、面试记录与筛选;
2.协助上级制定并实施员工培训计划，包括各项人事规章制度及员工手册等;
3.负责办理员工入离职和转正手续、社保公积金、人事档案的管理、保管、用工合同的签订;
4.负责全院员工的考勤，及时准确统计各项请假、休假、销假等有关事宜;
5.医护人员证件变更、注册材料办理;
6.完成上级交办的其它事务。

任职资格:
1、大专及以上学历，有2年以上医院、医疗行业人事工作背景优先;
2、较强的数据处理能力，熟练使用Offce等各类办公软件;
3、抗压能力强，有亲和力，工作细致认真，有较强的责任感，能够服从上级领导的工作安排。
